{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3e12d307-ce05-4fbf-8484-79914920c6d1","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nCheck for any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) and update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5758eaf0-3bfc-47b4-983b-18cbc5390269","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"B41C:1E6FAE:919DF7:B36BE8:6A01359B"},"id":"7fef2917-23ef-4d7e-bfd7-f2ca1dfb1fb6","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:49:22.578Z","parentId":"cb8e9ce9-e084-4249-b19c-8a3f826d881f"}
